From: Steve <steventhanhtuan@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 22:19:18 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 14/17] task4: LLM consolidation core, verified merge with
 archive-first commit protocol

coral/hub/consolidation.py: one-shot claude -p caller (injectable for
tests), TITLE/ATTEMPTS/BODY output contract with a strict parser,
content-derived group ids, atomic consolidations.json cache recording
both successes and failures (a failed member set never re-spends an
LLM call). run_consolidation_pass archives members first, publishes
the consolidated note as the atomic commit point, best-effort rolls
back on partial archive failure, wraps each group so nothing escapes,
and only ever publishes a note that passed mechanical verification of
every cited attempt score. Empty-evidence groups never consolidate.

Reviewed; one blocking issue (unguarded archive loop losing cache and
half-archiving) fixed with regression tests. 30 core tests green.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
